Defendant Anthony Wielochowski in court with attorney Zoe Everett.  Joy Hammond appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.  

Court made disclosure on the record.  Parties have no objection to this court proceeding on this matter.  Defendant changes his plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.   Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.  

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  Defendant sentenced to serve 6 MONTHS  in the House of Correction.  Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on Probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 1 YEAR.
Conditions: 
*  AODA assessment/treatment deemed necessary;
*  Mental health assessment/treatment deemed necessary;
*  Take all prescribed meds;
*  Referred to the Mental Health Unit of the probation department;
*  No contact with John S.;
*  Submit a DNA sample and pay the DNA surcharge or, if not paid, convert to a civil judgment;
*  Write a letter of apology to John S.  

Court WAIVED COSTS AND SURCHARGES.  Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief received and filed.
